Boil a large #pot{} of salted @water{to taste} and @salt{to taste} for the @Dried Orzo{170%grams}.

When boiling, add the @orzo to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pot.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, tear the @Smoked Salmon{100%grams} into large pieces.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw salmon.

Chop the @Tomato{2%unit}(chopped into 2cm cubes) into cubes.

Mix @Sun Dried Tomato Paste{1%sachet}, half the @Italian Herbs{1/2%sachet} and @Mayo{2%sachet} in a large #bowl{}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the orzo, @Salad Leaves{40%grams} and tomatoes to the bowl. Toss together to coat.

Arrange orzo salad in deep #plates{} or #bowls{}.

Top with smoked salmon and serve.